.class, so it should be covered. But for StAXResult, the code behaves differently, directly creating a new instance. Hmm, maybe my custom nested classes are causing compilation issues with the $ signs?\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating dynamic access instrumentation**\\\\n\\\\nI'm wondering about dynamic-access instrumentation possibly excluding reflections when a target class is outside the user code. Wait, does the call site get tracked if the target type is from metadata? Hmm, I think I found that active class dynamic access can scan all calls statically. Coverage is necessary for branches executed regardless of the target. I wonder if our tests aren't running because of the class name; JDBCSQLXMLTest is public.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering the testing process**\\\\n\\\\nI need to think about whether we should compile or run tests ourselves. The developer specifically mentioned we shouldn't do that. Instead, maybe there's a current build report or some problems from an external run after our attempt that could be inspected for results. It seems crucial to avoid running tests on our end for now. I'll look into the reports to see what we can learn from them.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_7Cq6Iqz7lV4s4bPBfIXTRoOu|fc_05680276128df6c50169f9820740bc819dad7602cb2354ead2\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"find tests/src/org.hsqldb/hsqldb/2.4.1/build -path '*TEST-*.xml' -type f -printf '%p\\\\n'\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 595, \"output\": 1147, \"cacheRead\": 33792, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 35534, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777959412170, \"responseId\": \"resp_05680276128df6c50169f981f4e240819db49c54a3acc3291c\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\",