aging user code filtering, especially for those nested classes.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering native image execution**\\\\n\\\\nI'm thinking about how tests should ideally run under Native Image by default, and using agent-generated metadata for nested test helper classes seems acceptable. I wonder if some tests might fail due to dependencies on custom helpers only when running with reflection. Should I consider removing the javax.xml.bind dependency? It seems HSQLDB tests ran fine with this dependency, but if the native image includes it, could that be an issue? Checking generated agent configs might not be necessary, but I should ensure that user-code-filter patterns accommodate nested class names with a dollar sign.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_QdF7HbPSIUGQ0vF4fh1Xa0gr|fc_05680276128df6c50169f9825b6494819dbb278a3571d19407\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"git diff -- tests/src/org.hsqldb/hsqldb/2.4.1/user-code-filter.json tests/src/org.hsqldb/hsqldb/2.4.1/build.gradle tests/src/org.hsqldb/hsqldb/2.4.1/src/test/java/org_hsqldb/hsqldb/JDBCSQLXMLTest.java | sed -n '1,240p'\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 336, \"output\": 1043, \"cacheRead\": 44544, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 45923, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777959500007, \"responseId\": \"resp_05680276128df6c50169f9824cbd38819d869106a5d33eb669\"}}\n4278:[tool-exec] start id=call_QdF7HbPSIUGQ0vF4fh1Xa0gr|fc_05680276128df6c50169f9825b6494819dbb278a3571d19407 name=bash args={\"command\": \"git diff -- tests/src/org.hsqldb/hsqldb/2.4.1/user-code-filter.json tests/src/org.hsqldb/hsqldb/2.4.1/build.gradle tests/src/org.hsqldb/hsqldb/2.4.1/src/test/java/org_hsqldb/hsqldb/JDBCSQLXMLTest.java | sed -n '1,240p'\"}\n4281:  diff --git i/tests/src/org.hsq