adata tied to nested classes. There's a question about whether generating native image configuration for these nested test classes, which use a dollar sign, is acceptable. Although it's generally advised to avoid `$` in test class names, it seems like I can restructure things by creating a single public top-level class instead. However, I may still need to ensure that the native image metadata captures test classes correctly while managing user code filtering, especially for those nested classes.\\n\\n**Considering native image execution**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how tests should ideally run under Native Image by default, and using agent-generated metadata for nested test helper classes seems acceptable. I wonder if some tests might fail due to dependencies on custom helpers only when running with reflection. Should I consider removing the javax.xml.bind dependency? It seems HSQLDB tests ran fine with this dependency, but if the native image includes it, could that be an issue? Checking generated agent configs might not be necessary, but I should ensure that user-code-filter patterns accommodate nested class names with a dollar sign.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_05680276128df6c50169f9824d5c34819daa699656d9abd6f7\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-YJbMjbhMQuh7zIl4xgGidbhoM-PJlz1TW_kwWLVM97figREYNuWsCNQCXeR_Bi82pQr-5sbpO56GWqlvCOpuyxfv-k0ZiDHvw-9b7vanaDScJj_V2EgQRZYrjJgBSK58bnK1f6MWKhvYeU2uZcrc-K-s7TUjDSXHC-rPFYqGUaiY9Fq7qvFiU03Buuff0_TTQZLJJq3N5mk8GFi8x5qcoWiLT0QmG0FOGutU_auMAQZtHAwcQny136XmGswM49oWS3Rrgj-voyHCSSThim1ndAX_3-eHjx1VM2Jl3xSLhFH4jdpIpSGjpWW2UuMMW7oVysQ0FKAMpxUSCLDRFfmh76ZO_-9-ove60KhdWCxe6jglJ9qQpnZrSl3KeTmJAWPIewnBrfi_5WNjqD3BnYvqjhsd4JOPkfLxW3fNhsWqQ1YSN4KH1bNJ50HPD4ZoK05cwLHesz-5r8KaGEqhxYP_4TY2Mmtxitt_RSWUAzf4emfl4JXewkLvGzdDWMhoezdyiUhHI0W_cah9f2dlD6A0PC6weTo8977O0fbYNNn3tZ0j6yLmbtETEqId1TZsYyKKzh9aVDh2yFxL8UJ7aF_cDrNgFzO4qOZhaEufUxs54bDjELNWCdsCxcUfzoo-Z-UgIax1Tcfbfx9IrSurQIbcWZLKmW6fb8RM8hbG